news.title: Kanakia, Hines, Mitsubishi Estate & Sumitomo Corporation's JV to develop office space in Mumbai
news.para: The office space spread across three-acre land parcel and will offer 1.5 million sq ft. The project is being designed by Kohn Pedersen Fox (KPF).

news.title: Karnataka: Rules to tax unauthorised properties in rural areas soon
news.para: The move is part of measures to implement The Karnataka Gram Swaraj and Panchayat Raj (Amendment) Bill, 2025, which was passed in March.

news.title: Mussoorie Dehradun development body to identify land bank for residential projects
news.para: This move was prompted by the rising population density and the success of previous initiatives such as the ISBT and Aamwala Tarla residential schemes.

news.title: Ranchi civic body issues notices to PMAY beneficiaries over dues
news.para: The LHP consists of 1,008 flats spread over 5.33 acres at Aani in Dhurwa. Each flat cost around Rs 13 lakh, of which Rs 6.5 lakh was subsidised by the Union and the state govts. The rest was to be given by the beneficiaries in five instalments.

news.title: Bhubaneswar: Residents file complaint against builder for occupying common areas in project
news.para: According to the complaint filed with the executive magistrate, the developer allegedly entered the premises on May 23 and demolished a boundary wall and gate in the common area.

news.title: Illegal commercial structures demolished in Kharar, Zirakpur
news.para: In Kharar, a commercial building in Gillco Valley, Sector 115, was razed after it was found to be constructed without an approved layout plan from the executive officer's office and lacking mandatory Rera registration.

news.title: NGT asks environment ministry to frame guidelines for plywood industry
news.para: The green body was hearing a matter regarding several plywood units causing pollution in a village in Yamuna Nagar district of Haryana.

news.title: No change in property tax rates, higher bills automatically due to RR rate revision: BMC
news.para: "The current revision comes after a 10-year gap. There is a legal provision that these payments will be automatically revised due to the changes made in the ready reckoner for the financial year 2025-26," the release stated.

news.title: NBCC India's net profit rises 29.10% in Q4 FY25
news.para: NBCC India has incorporated a wholly-owned subsidiary named NBCC Overseas Real Estate LLC in Dubai Mainland, (UAE) on April 23, 2025 for carrying out real estate business.

news.title: ED says DHFL promoters used public money for extravagant hobbies, lavish purchases
news.para: The Wadhawan brothers are accused of defrauding a consortium of 17 banks led by Union Bank of India (UBI) to the tune of Rs 34,615 crore.

news.title: Prestige Estates Projects posts net profit of ₹43.10 crore in Q4 FY25
news.para: Prestige Estates Projects' net consolidated total income stood at ₹1,589.30 crore in Q4 FY25, a dip of 28.81 per cent from ₹2,232.50 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: JCB India eyes 8–9% growth, plans to invest ₹200–250 crore in FY26
news.para: JCB India invested ₹500 crore in FY25 and has earmarked another ₹200–250 crore this year, primarily towards tooling, R&D, and digital innovation.

news.title: Sunteck Realty to develop residential project on 2.5 acres land in Mumbai
news.para: Sunteck Realty expects to currently generate a free sale component of about 2,75,000 sq ft from the development and redevelopment of the project.

news.title: Indian construction equipment industry achieves marginal 3% growth in FY25: Report
news.para: During the current fiscal, while the domestic construction equipment market growth remained subdued at 2.7%, the industry's overall performance was better due to a 10% surge observed in the exports.

news.title: Sobha posts net profit of ₹40.85 crore in Q4 FY25
news.para: Sobha 's net consolidated total income stood at ₹1,270.73 crore in Q4 FY25, a growth of 60.60 per cent from ₹791.25 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Goa government simplifies process for bifurcation of house numbers
news.para: The issuance of a house number to an applicant is to give a separate identity to the said portion of the house and is merely fiscal in nature for taxation purposes.

news.title: Noida authority cracks down on societies with no waste treatment plants
news.para: Under the Solid Waste Management (SWM) Rules, 2016, waste treatment plants are a must for group housing societies built on plots spanning 5,000 sqm or more.

news.title: County Group acquires 13.3-acre land in Wave City NH24, Ghaziabad for ₹400 crores
news.para: The smart city by Wave group is adjacent to NH-24 and spans over 4,200 acres and the firm had earlier sold land parcels to realty developers to raise fund.

news.title: Bengaluru: BDA's lapse leaves 300 families of Banashankari layout on shaky land
news.para: More than 300 sites of 60ftx40ft dimension have been carved out from the land under dispute. Now, a huge question mark hangs over the future of these sites and houses built on them.

news.title: Indore: Residential project proposed at seven hectare of Hukumchand Mill land
news.para: "An architect is already appointed for this ambitious housing scheme to come up at Hukumchand Mill land," said Indore divisional commissioner Deepak Singh.
